      • query

        default GC query(String query,
                 PatternMatchingAlgorithm algorithm,
                 boolean returnEmbeddings)
        Matches a given pattern on a graph collection. The boolean flag returnEmbeddings specifies, if the return shall be the input graphs with a new property AddMatchesToProperties.DEFAULT_KEY, or a new collection consisting of the constructed embeddings.
        Parameters:
        query - the query pattern in GDL syntax
        algorithm - custom pattern matching algorithm, e.g., DepthSearchMatching
        returnEmbeddings - if true it returns the embeddings as a new graph collection if false it returns the input collection with a new property with key AddMatchesToProperties.DEFAULT_KEY and value true/false if the pattern is contained in the respective graph
        Returns:
        a graph collection containing either the embeddings or the input graphs with a new property with name AddMatchesToProperties.DEFAULT_KEY

      • verify

        default GC verify()
        Verifies each graph of this collection, removing dangling edges, i.e. edges pointing to or from a vertex not contained in the graph.
        This operator can be applied after an operator that has not checked these graphs validity. The graph heads of these base graphs remains unchanged.
        Returns:
        this graph collection with all dangling edges removed.

      • verifyGraphsContainment

        default GC verifyGraphsContainment()
        Verifies this graph collection, removing dangling graph ids from its elements, i.e. ids not contained in the collection.
        This operator can be applied after an operator that has not checked the graphs validity. The graph head of this graph collection remains unchanged.
        Returns:
        this graph collection with all dangling graph ids removed.

      • intersectWithSmallResult

        default GC intersectWithSmallResult(GC otherCollection)
        Returns a collection with all base graphs that exist in both input collections. Graph equality is based on their identifiers.

        Implementation that works faster if otherCollection is small (e.g. fits in the workers main memory).

        Parameters:
        otherCollection - collection to build intersect with
        Returns:
        intersection of both collections

      • difference

        default GC difference(GC otherCollection)
        Returns a collection with all base graphs that are contained in that collection but not in the other. Graph equality is based on their identifiers.
        Parameters:
        otherCollection - collection to subtract from that collection
        Returns:
        difference between that and the other collection

      • differenceWithSmallResult

        default GC differenceWithSmallResult(GC otherCollection)
        Returns a collection with all base graphs that are contained in that collection but not in the other. Graph equality is based on their identifiers.

        Alternate implementation that works faster if the intermediate result (list of graph identifiers) fits into the workers memory.

        Parameters:
        otherCollection - collection to subtract from that collection
        Returns:
        difference between that and the other collection

      • equalsByGraphElementData

        default org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<Boolean> equalsByGraphElementData(GC otherCollection)
        Returns a 1-element dataset containing a boolean value which indicates if the graph collection is equal to the given graph collection.

        Equality is defined on the element data contained inside the collection, i.e. vertices and edges. This is limited to EPGM data (IDs, Label, Properties). All extensions of EPGM are ignored.

        Parameters:
        otherCollection - graph collection to compare with
        Returns:
        1-element dataset containing true if the two collections are equal or false if not

      • equalsByGraphData

        default org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<Boolean> equalsByGraphData(GC otherCollection)
        Returns a 1-element dataset containing a boolean value which indicates if the graph collection is equal to the given graph collection.

        Equality is defined on the data contained inside the collection, i.e. graph heads, vertices and edges. This is limited to EPGM data (IDs, Label, Properties). All extensions of EPGM are ignored.

        Parameters:
        otherCollection - graph collection to compare with
        Returns:
        1-element dataset containing true if the two collections are equal or false if not
